This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it proposes a new parallel method for k-means clustering using MapReduce. It is also likely to belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as k-means is a popular clustering method used in data mining. Additionally, it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as k-means is a commonly used unsupervised learning algorithm. The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a new preprocessing stage using k-d tree. Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category is a possibility as k-means is often used in image segmentation and clustering.
